2. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The proposed algorithm, League Championship Algorithm, is a population-based algorithmic framework for global optimization, which falls under the category of evolutionary computing. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses various scheduling algorithms and their performance in minimizing makespan time, which is related to the design and analysis of algorithms. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper deals with scheduling tasks in IaaS cloud, which involves control and management of resources in a system. 
5. cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper proposes a new algorithm for task scheduling, which involves programming and implementation of the algorithm.
